



She was only a teenager when she was trafficked into the sex trade. She was promised a better life, but instead she was forced to work in brothels and strip clubs. She was abused and raped by customers, and she was often beaten by her pimps. She thought she would never escape, but she was eventually rescued by police and social workers. Now she is working to help other victims of trafficking. She is a powerful advocate for change, and she is helping to create a world where no one will ever have to suffer the horrors of trafficking again.
